HP Ge detector of 20% efficiency (in ratio to

The position of targets inside the accelerator
was chosen in accordance with known calibrations to
provide the beam energy values of 650, 450 and 300 MeV
at different irradiations.
All detail see in original paper.
Gamma-spectroscopy  measurements of irradiated
samples have been started after "cooling" for one
month because of high activity of short lived
radionuclides accumulated during the activation.
Table of Isotopes, 8th Edition, Wiley, New York, 1996.
The spectroscopic properties of the nuclides were
taken from the 'Table of Isotopes' (see above) and for
some cases from the 'Nuclear Data Sheets' compilation.
Two target were used: nat-W and 97% enriched 186-W
material that supplied in a form of metal pieces about
1.5 mm thick. They were fixed to the Al holder with 50
mum foil of nat-W used as a support.
The standard deviation for any individual yield
value is defined by the statistical error of the
corresponded gamma-line area and by the systematical
errors.  The latter ones are arising due to the
absolute calibration of the yields, the inaccuracy on
the measured efficiency of detectors and the errors on
the tabular standards like quantum yields of
characteristic gamma-ray lines belonging to the
individual nuclides.
